            <section xml:id="d1/df3/class_modular_1_1_scoped_reference_1a0062182e784719a983ed0e17f7f81945">
                <title>__construct ($object, callable $onDestruct)</title> <emphasis></emphasis>
                
<para>Save a reference to the object and the callable to call when this <link linkend="d1/df3/class_modular_1_1_scoped_reference">ScopedReference</link> falls out of scope..</para>

<para>
                <formalpara>
                    <title/>
                    <table frame="all">
                        <title>Parameters</title>
                        <tgroup cols="2" align="left" colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                        <tbody>
                            <row>
                                <entry>$object</entry>
                                <entry>
<para>to track during lifetime of this instance of <link linkend="d1/df3/class_modular_1_1_scoped_reference">ScopedReference</link> </para>
</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry>$onDestruct</entry>
                                <entry>
<para>(takes single parameter which will be the object being referenced). </para>
</entry>
                            </row>
                        </tbody>
                        </tgroup>
                    </table>
                </formalpara>
                </para>

            </section>
            <section xml:id="d1/df3/class_modular_1_1_scoped_reference_1a421831a265621325e1fdd19aace0c758">
                <title>__destruct ()</title> <emphasis></emphasis>
                
<para>Calls the destruct callable passed in constructor passing the object as first parameter </para>

